RTC.Description: Sets new target volume. Provide the target volume as 8 bit index value to be mapped through a tunable VolumeTable. To use slope-based ramping: ---------------------------------- When db_per_second has a non-zero value,ramp_milliseconds is ignored and db_per_second controls the ramp. To use time-based ramping: ---------------------------------- The value of db_per_second must be zero for ramp milliseconds to then control the ramping.
Contains the value indicated by the surround knob.

Command a mute by specifying whether mute is active (non zero mute_switch) or inactive (mute_switch is "0"). If db_per_second is non-zero, it commands the timing of the mute, otherwise the ramp_milliseconds is used.

Provide the target value as a 32-bit signed integer index value (to be mapped through a tunable calibration into a normalized float between -1 and 1). To use slope-based ramping: ---------------------------------- When db_per_second has a non-zero value,ramp_milliseconds is ignored and db_per_second controls the ramp. To use time-based ramping: ---------------------------------- The value of db_per_second must be zero for ramp milliseconds to then control the ramping.
